comments: Jackson Jr. (MEM) fails to fully clear and is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Thompson (GSW) brings his hand toward Morant's (MEM) left side and marginal contact occurs as Morant elevates for the shot attempt.
Wiggins (GSW) firms up over his right foot and absorbs the side-to-side contact that occurs with Brooks (MEM) as he goes over the pick.
Curry (GSW) and Brooks (MEM) come together during the drive and marginal contact occurs as Curry releases his off-arm away from Brooks' front to move toward the wing.
Morant (MEM) jumps toward Payton II (GSW) to contest the layup attempt and marginal contact occurs with Payton II's (GSW) extended right arm after the release.
Thompson (GSW) engages and disengages with Clarke (MEM) as Clarke moves to set the pick.

Clarke (MEM) establishes himself in a screening position in Payton II's (GSW) path and absorbs the contact. Clarke and Payton II then briefly engage and disengage with one another after the initial contact occurs.
Thompson (GSW) is turning alongside Morant's (MEM) path and marginal body contact occurs as Morant contorts away from the basket during the driving shot attempt.
Morant (MEM) grasps and then quickly releases Thompson's (GSW) left arm as Thompson defends the driving shot attempt.
Clarke (MEM) brings his hands toward Payton II's (GSW) back and marginal contact occurs as the rebound falls to the opposite side of the lane.
Clarke (MEM) and Jackson Jr. (MEM) each make clean contact with the ball and dislodge it away from Wiggins (GSW) prior to incidental arm contact occurring during rebounding.
Clarke's (MEM) left leg is slightly extended outward when incidental contact occurs with Payton II (GSW) as Payton II retrieves the rebound.
Clarke (MEM) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges the ball away prior to incidental arm contact occurring with Wiggins (GSW).
Thompson (GSW) and Clarke (MEM) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Replay review of the out of bounds call pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Wiggins (GSW) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds and possession is awarded to Memphis.
Payton II (GSW) is firming up over his right foot and absorbs the contact that occurs with Brooks (MEM) as the pick is set.
Brooks (MEM) makes clean contact with the ball and partially dislodges it away from Payton II (GSW) prior to any incidental arm contact occurring.
After Payton II (GSW) re-gains full control of the ball, Brooks (MEM) moves forward slightly toward him and marginal arm/body contact occurs as Payton II turns to pass.

Payton II (GSW) is in the lane for less than three seconds prior to the ball being dislodged by Brooks (MEM). After Payton II re-gains control, he is in the lane for less than three seconds before passing the ball and exiting the lane.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) and Wiggins (GSW) make incidental foot-to-foot contact with one another during rebounding.
Poole (GSW) gathers the ball and takes two steps before releasing the pass.
Brooks (MEM) brings his hands forward toward Wiggins' (GSW) back and marginal contact occurs as Wiggins elevates for the rebound.
Morant (MEM) makes contact with the part of Wiggins' (GSW) hand that is on the ball and legally contests the put-back attempt.
Wiggins (GSW) mishandles the ball and loses control of it prior to incidental arm contact being made by Bane (MEM).
Morant (MEM) and Payton II (GSW) each extend an arm backward in pursuit of the rebound and incidental arm contact occurs.

Brooks (MEM) and Thompson (GSW) each extend forward in pursuit of the rebound and each make clean contact with the ball prior to incidental body contact occurring. Brooks and Thompson then tie one another up on the floor and a jump ball is correctly assessed.
Payton II (GSW) brings his hand toward Clarke's (MEM) back and marginal contact occurs as Clarke's momentum is already causing him to fall out of bounds.

Clarke (MEM) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds. It was deemed Clarke had full control of the ball prior to him landing out of bounds and the shot clock was reset to 24 upon GSW gaining possession.
Wiggins (GSW) firms up over his left foot and absorbs the contact with Bane (MEM) as the screen is set.

Curry (GSW) brings his right hand down and makes clean contact with the ball before brushing Morant's (MEM) left elbow after his gather. Curry then raises his left hand up and cleanly dislodges the ball away from Morant thereafter.
Curry (GSW) splits his feet at the start of his dribble.
Morant (MEM) commits a take foul on Poole (GSW). Any contact thereafter is deemed immaterial.
Lee (GSW) establishes himself in a screening position in Melton's (MEM) path and absorbs the contact as the defensive switch takes place.
Brooks (MEM) and Payton II (GSW) make incidental arm contact with one another as they each elevate for the rebound.
Clarke (MEM) commits a take foul on Thompson (GSW).
Curry (GSW) releases his forearm away from Clarke's (MEM) back and marginal contact occurs as Clarke's momentum is carrying him out of bounds.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: A jump ball is assessed as the crew is not able to determine who touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds in real time. The play was not reviewable because a Coach?s Challenge is the only mechanism to trigger replay review of out-of-bounds violations. However, Brooks (MEM) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds and possession should have been awarded to Golden State.
Thompson (GSW) and Clarke (MEM) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Payton II (GSW) and Morant (MEM) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Payton II (GSW) makes contact with the backboard as he follows through on his shot contest. The ball does not make an unnatural bounce as a result of Payton II's contact with the backboard.
Thompson (GSW) maintains a rested forearm on Morant's (MEM) front and marginal contact occurs as Morant contorts away from the basket during the driving shot attempt.
